snippet.textDisplay: I have to say that these girls are pretty talented. They have great charisma and an awesome potential to dance. It is quite obvious that this IS ryujin's era but it does not neglect the fact that every girl shined in their own different way. JYP knows which concept suits every girl based on their personality and how well they can perform the whole concept, which i dont think is that easy. Although yeji is my ultimate bias, I have been attracted more by yuna and chaeryong they have really shine the most for me personally.Also the bside's slap really hard, the mixture of sounds between each of them is really unique and somenthing I had never listen un kpop before. Definitely one of the Best comebacks of 2020 up to now and hopefully the girls can get all the wins they deserve.
snippet.textOriginal: I have to say that these girls are pretty talented. They have great charisma and an awesome potential to dance. It is quite obvious that this IS ryujin's era but it does not neglect the fact that every girl shined in their own different way. JYP knows which concept suits every girl based on their personality and how well they can perform the whole concept, which i dont think is that easy. Although yeji is my ultimate bias, I have been attracted more by yuna and chaeryong they have really shine the most for me personally.Also the bside's slap really hard, the mixture of sounds between each of them is really unique and somenthing I had never listen un kpop before. Definitely one of the Best comebacks of 2020 up to now and hopefully the girls can get all the wins they deserve.

snippet.textDisplay:
Lia represents how people see her only as a rich girl and she's kicking away all the stereotypes and hate.
Yuna represents how she's the maknae and isn't used to the cameras but then she gets comfortable.
Yeji represents how idols are all assumed to act and she's being herself.
Chaeryoung represents how she ran away from the hate comments but shot them down with her talent.
Ryujin represents her self-growth journey from when she scouted at a fanmeet to where she is now.

ITZY represents how important self-love is.
